Starting something from the ground up is never an easy task 🦋 as some of you know I’ve been promoting my new summer intensive. And to be so vulnerably honest, the initial idea of starting something of my own was and still is terrifying. 

The idea of creating @existdance came to me years ago and through telling friends, and hearing their support it really pushed me to finally begin the journey. It’s been a slow process over the course of a few months but I really am proud of my progress 🥹

I wanted to take the time to the thank the people who have been by my side with this idea from the beginning. Surrounding myself with people who want to see you win has been my biggest motivator, and blessing honestly. 

With that being said, this is fully funded by myself and primarily through the registration from students. If you or anyone you know is interested please don’t hesitate to reach out to me ❤️ There are options to do 1, 2, or all 3 days August 25th - 27th held at @generationsdancecompany in Dunellen, Nj

Register today at 
www.existdanceworkshops.com

If you feel inspired please share this post with your friends, studio owners, and parents! The faculty line up is beyond incredible and I am so honored to know each one of them 💕 don’t miss out on this opportunity! 

Photo by the incredible @motiontoast
